tally and soundlessly, the =\r\nSavitur Gayatri mantra. Within less than 20-30 japas of the mantra, he felt=\r\n/saw - and I describe it as he told me - an unbroken steam of tremendous, p=\r\nure, flood of Golden Light above his head. Like a world above and outside o=\r\nur world. Intensely pure, intensely Divine. The eventual idea, he told me, =\r\nwas to enter into that stream of Light above and see things from that persp=\r\nective. But as long as there are impurities in the mind and body, it is not=\r\n possible to enter into that realm easily. The gunas must be in a stable eq=\r\nuilibrium. Neither the laziness of Tamas, nor the impatience of rajas is co=\r\nnducive for it, but the stable, illuminating, self-assurance of satwa leadi=\r\nng to a deeper\nequanimity in mind and life is needed.\n\nApparently, he also =\r\nrealized that there are some Tantrik mantras of Ma which serve a similar pu=\r\nrpose as the Gayatri mantra. They take a person to the spiritual planes abo=\r\nve.\n\nSo I asked him why did you not continue the meditation or japa of Gaya=\r\ntri mantra, since there was a nice experience. He said it would have pulled=\r\n him in and he would not have been able to continue the spiritual practices=\r\n which he was already doing for some time, and leaving something half way i=\r\ns not good.\n\nReading the explanation your provided below, that is : \n\n&quot;We m=\r\neditate upon that Savitaa (yaH) who impels (prachodayaat) our (naH) \nthough=\r\nts (dhiyaH). He blesses us with subtle eyesight. Without his \nlight, we wou=\r\nld not be able to distinguish different objects. This is \nexplained in the =\r\nAitaterya Upanishad =E2=80=9CThe sun, having become eyesight, \nentered the =\r\neyes=E2=80=9D. He thus blesses all living beings.&quot;\n\n.. matches with the des=\r\ncription that I had heard from my friend. Quite interesting!\n\n-Regards\n Raj=\r\narshi\n\n \n\nawaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAwamajAna=\r\nnto mamAwyayama