mitted here ].  We me=\r\nditate upon the splendor of the sun, which is vareNyam.\n \nWe meditate upon =\r\nthat Savitaa (yaH) who impels (prachodayaat) our (naH) thoughts (dhiyaH). H=\r\ne blesses us with subtle eyesight. Without his light, we would not be able =\r\nto distinguish different objects. This is explained in the Aitaterya Upanis=\r\nhad =E2=80=9CThe sun, having become eyesight, entered the eyes=E2=80=9D. He=\r\n thus blesses all living beings. \n \n----\n \nSent from Windows Mail\n \nReply t=\r\no sender . Reply to group . Reply via Web Post . All Messages (2) . Top ^ 2=\r\na Re: Jayaadi homam Mon Jan 7, 2013 11:24 am (PST) . Posted by: &quot;Narasimha =\r\nPVR Rao&quot; pvr108 \nNamaste,\n\nThis is correct. Traditionally, Jayadi homam is =\r\nperformed as a part of \nUttarangam (concluding offerings). One can include =\r\nthis in any homam. If \nyou follow the homam manuals on my website, make off=\r\nerings with the \nmantras of Jayaadi homam just before the offerings mention=\r\ned under \n&quot;Uttarangam&quot; in the manuals (offerings to Fire, Wind, Sun, C=\r\nreator, \nSustainer and Destroyer).\n\nVeda mantras of Jayaadi homam make offe=\r\nrings to various celestial beings \nthat support our lives. It is a really n=\r\nice set of mantras, but suitable \nonly for those who who are comfortable wi=\r\nth Vedic intonation and also \nthose who have a lot of time. If you do a 4 h=\r\nour homam, having a 20 \nminute wrap up by making offerings to various being=\r\ns makes sense. If you \nhave only 30 minutes, you are better off focusing on=\r\n the main deity. If \nGanapathi, Chandi, Vishnu etc are pleased (i.e. main c=\r\nhosen deity for \nhomam), other beings will also eventually be pleased. The =\r\nbasic wrap up \n(Fire, Wind, Sun, Creator, Sustainer & Destroyer) are suffic=\r\nient. There \nis no need for an extended wrap up.\n\nHowever, it will be very =\r\nnice if some people with time, energy and \nproficiency in Vedic intonated c=\r\nhanting c