 few other Ganapathi mantras that can =\r\nbe useful to some people here. If \nyou like any of them, you may offer them=\r\n to Ganapathi in fire in your \nGanapathi (or some other) homam. If mantra h=\r\nas no &quot;svAhA&quot; at the end, \nadd it to make an offering in fire. If it alread=\r\ny has a svAhA at the \nend, offer it as is and there is no need to add anoth=\r\ner svAhA.\n\n(1) Buddhi Ganapathi mantra (for intellectual sharpness and good=\r\n \nspeech): OM aiM gaM vAggaNapataye namaH\n(2) Guru Ganapathi mantra (to bri=\r\nng one&#39;s guru): OM gaM gaNapataye \nsarva-vighna-harAya sarvAya sarva-gurave=\r\n lambodarAya hrIM gaM namaH\n(3) Soura Ganapathi mantra (to cure diseases): =\r\nOM jyoM saH saH jyoM \nghR^iNissUrya Aditya OM OM shrIM hrIM klIM glauM gaM =\r\ngaNapate \nvara-varada jyOM saH sarva-rogAn hara hara saH jyOM svAhA\n(4) Nil=\r\nakantha Ganapathi mantra (to remove poisons from body): OM proM \nOM shrIM h=\r\nrIM klIM glauM gaM nrIM gaNapate vara-varada ThaH sarva viShaM \nme nAshaya =\r\nsvAhA\n(5) Vidya Ganapathi mantra (for good learning): aiM blUM OM shrIM hrI=\r\nM \nklIM glauM gaM aiM blUM gaNapate vara-varada aiM blUM vidyAm dehi svAhA\n=\r\n(6) Sankatahara Ganapathi mantra (when one is in serious troubles): \nshrIM =\r\nOM gaNapataye namo varavarada me \npratibandha-R^iNa-dAridrya-roga-saMkaTAn =\r\nnivAraya svAhA\n(7) Rina Hara Ganapthi mantra (for relief from debts): OM ga=\r\nNesha R^iNaM \nChindhi vareNyaM huM namaH phaT (aggressive version)\n(8) Rina=\r\n Mochana Ganapthi mantra (for relief from debts): OM glAM \nR^iNa-mochana ga=\r\nNadhipataye namaH (gentler version)\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstro=\r\nlogy & Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n\nOn =\r\nThu, Jan 3, 2013 at 2:41 AM, seeking wrote:\n\nThank you very much for your a=\r\nnswer, Shree Narasimha.\n\nIn the internet I found more than 1 &quot;Lakshmi Ganap=\r\nathi&quot; mantra.\n\nOne is the very one I have seen in the m