tation technique that can be=\r\n specifically applied to Vishnu Sahasra nama and it is mentioned in preface=\r\n of VSN itself (yaani naamaani gauNani vikhyaataani mahatmanah). Here gauNa=\r\n does not mean minor. It means &quot;being related to guna&quot;. It means each name =\r\nextolls one (several actually) attributes of Vishnu. One can ponder over th=\r\nat quality of Vishnu as that name comes up. It takes up time to practice su=\r\nch technique and requires quite a bit of cross reference reading. It is to =\r\nbe slowly developed over time. But it is very effective. \nRegards, Srikanth=\r\n \n--- In vedic-wisdom@ yahoogroups. com, Narasimha PVR Rao wrote: &gt; &gt; &gt; Nam=\r\naste, &gt; &gt; First, on Ranga&#39;s question: &gt; &gt; There is no single &quot;effective&quo=\r\n t; way. Whether one is chanting oneself or &gt; listening to a person/cassett=\r\ne/ CD/MP3, is not the primary factor. The &gt; primary factor is how focused o=\r\nne&#39;s mind is on it. The goal of chanting &gt; a stotra or a mantra is to elimi=\r\nnate or atleast limit other thoughts and &gt; focus the mind on it. That can h=\r\nappen with chanting as well as &gt; listening. &gt; &gt; For example, I may be chant=\r\ning Vishnu sahasra nama stotra and yet my &gt; mind may be wandering everywher=\r\ne and focusing on all kind of dirty &gt; thoughts. Another person listening to=\r\n me while doing some chores may be &gt; focusing a good part of their mental a=\r\nttention on the prayer and &gt; contemplating each word and its meaning and co=\r\nntemplating the qualities &gt; of Lord. In that case, that listener will get a=\r\n lot more benefit from it &gt; than I will! &gt; &gt; Each deity has some\nqualities.=\r\n Focusing the mind on a deity and his/her &gt; mantra increases those qualitie=\r\ns, over time, in one&#39;s own mind and in &gt; one&#39;s surroundings. If a lot of sa=\r\ndhakas with good concentration worship &gt; Chandi in this world, there may be=\r\n a lot of violent outrage and fierce &gt; fight against adharma in this world.=\r\n If a lot of sadhakas with good &gt; concentration worship Vishnu, there may b=\r\ne an upsurge of calm, &gt; self-assured and confident sattwa in the fight for =\r\nestablishing dharma. &gt; These energies balance each other. World is probably=\r\n in a transition &gt; phase right now and worshippers of Chandi are needed. Bu=\r\nt, soon, we will &gt; need a lot more people worshipping Vishnu. &gt; &gt; By the wa=\r\ny, good sadhakas worshipping Ganesha increase the sense of &gt; stability and =\r\ngroundedness in the world. &gt; &gt; Second: Anushtup is the metre with 8 syllabl=\r\nes per line and 4 lines per &gt; verse. Whole Vishnu sahasra naama stotra is i=\r\nn anushtup metre. &gt; Traditionally, one specific verse is\nsaid to be equival=\r\nent to reading &gt; all 1000 names: &gt; &gt; shrIrAma rAma rAmeti. rame rAme manora=\r\nme. &gt; sahasra nAma tattulyaM. rAma nAma vrAnane.. &gt; &gt; Actually, this verse =\r\nmeans that chanting &quot;shrIrAma rAma rAma&quot; mantra &gt; (known as Amrita mantra) =\r\nis equivalent to chanting 1000 names. &gt; &gt; However, don&#39;t take it as a short=\r\ncut. If one is lazy and unfocused, &gt; chanting this verse even 100 times may=\r\n do nothing. First, engage in some &gt; regular practices to remove laziness, =\r\ninstill discipline and sincerity, &gt; and get a state of mind where you can f=\r\nocus well on god. THEN the above &gt; 7-letter mantra can be as effective as 1=\r\n000 names. &gt; &gt; Best regards, &gt; Narasimha &gt; -------- &gt; Astrology & Spiritual=\r\nity Resources: http://www.VedicAst rologer.org&gt; -------- \n\nReply to sender =\r\n. Reply to group . Reply via Web Post . All Messages (4) . Top ^ Visit Your=\r\n Group &gt; View All Topics &gt; Create New Topic &gt; 5 New Members &gt; \nWe are makin=\r\ng changes based on your feedback, Thank you ! Submit Feedback &gt; The Yahoo! =\r\nGroups Product Blog Check it out! &gt; GROUP FOOT